[2] Venezuela (Miranda)
Date: Sat 30 Jan 2010
Source: Entorno Inteligente [in Spanish, trans, Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.entornointeligente.com/resumen/resumen.php?items=1008400>


In epidemiological week 3, from 17-23 Jan [2010], Corposalud
[Corporacion de Salud; Health Corporation, a state health agency],
counted 28 new dengue cases in the entire region. The statistical
document indicated that of the 28 cases, only 9 were in the subregion,
of these 6 were in Gualcaipuro and 3 in Carrizal. There were cases in
the Paez municipality, 4 in Acevedo, 3 in Independencia, 2 in Andres
Bello, one in Brion, one in Lander, one in Paz Castillo, one in Simon
Bolivar, one in Sucre and one in Zamora.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT <promed@promedmail.org>

[Through Epidemiological Week 48 of 2009, Venezuela reported to PAHO a
DHF rate of 7.6 per cent, and the presence of all 4 dengue serotypes.
- Mod.JW]

