[3] Brazil (Minas Gerais)
Date: Fri 29 Jan 2010
Source: O Globo [in Portuguese, trans, Mod.TY, edited]
<http://oglobo.globo.com/cidades/mat/2010/01/29/autoridades-alertam-para-aumento-de-casos-de-dengue-em-belo-horizonte-915743924.asp>


Belo Horizonte now has 208 confirmed dengue cases just since the
beginning of this year [2010]. The situation is considered serious and
led the health authorities to reinforce prevention measures. The
measures are being adopted because the numbers of cases of dengue
fever will tend to greatly increase from now on. Officials said the
infestation by the mosquito that transmits dengue [virus] in Belo
Horizonte has reached worrying rates. According to the Ministry of
Health, _Aedes aegypti_ larvae should be found, at most, in one
percent of the residences. In the capital, the average is 4.2 percent.
The [_Aedes aegypti_] infestations also are of concern to
municipalities in the metropolitan region.

In Igarape, the [household infestation] index reached 4.3 percent. In
addition to house inspections, the city is applying insecticide and
collecting blood samples from the population to investigate the type
of dengue virus that is circulating at the beginning of year [2010].
[To date], 9 cases were confirmed in the city.

--
