[4] Brazil (Sao Paulo, Ribeirao Preto)
Date: Thu 28 Jan 2010
Source: EPTV [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.jornalacidade.com.br/editorias/cidades/2010/01/29/ribeirao-preto-chega-a-506-casos-de-dengue.html>


Confirmed dengue cases in Ribeirao Preto reached 506 in the 1st 29
days of the year [2010]. The city also has 858 suspected [dengue
cases] that await [laboratory] tests; only 73 have been discounted [as
negative] up to now.

The city is on the path to an epidemic because it needs to have 300
[dengue] cases per 100 000 inhabitants [to be classified as in
epidemic status], according to the state Secretariat of Health.
According to IBGE [Instituto Brasileiro de Geografia e Estatistica;
Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics], the city has 563 000
inhabitants. Taking these data into consideration, the municipality
needs to register 1689 dengue cases to have a confirmed epidemic. If
all the cases awaiting results are positive, Ribeirao now is close to
this number, as it would have 1364 cases in just this month of January
2010.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT <promed@promedmail.org>

[The number of dengue cases in Ribeirao Preto increased from 452 to
506 since 19 Jan 2010 (see ProMED archive no. 20100125.0277).

An interactive map showing the location of Ribeirao Preto in Sao Paulo
state can be accessed at
<http://www.maplandia.com/brazil/sao-paulo/ribeirao-preto/ribeirao-preto/>.

