[5] Brazil (Sao Paulo municipality)
Date: Fri 29 Jan 2010
Source: Portal O Taboaense [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.otaboanense.com.br/noticia/1907/epidemia-de-dengue-assusta-bairros-vizinhos-de-tabo%C3%83%C2%A3o-da-serra/>


Sao Paulo [city] neighborhoods neighboring Taboao da Serra are in a
state of alert due to dengue. Campo Limpo, Butanta and Morumbi are
among the risk areas where hundreds of [dengue] cases have now been
recorded this year [2010]. According to the Zoonoses Coordinator in
our city, Clovis Jose de Sa, help by everyone is needed to avoid an
outbreak that could be a problem in Taboao.

Taboao da Serra is considered to have been infested [by _Aedes
aegypti_?] since 2002, and we have transmission sporadically in the
months of January - May annually, due to the arrival of imported cases
from other municipalities and states in the holiday months. In order
to identify the localities having the greatest risk of an outbreak of
this disease, the state government uses an indicator called the
Breteau index when it is above one; this is to say mosquito larvae
were found in more than one house for each 100 houses inspected [the
areas are at risk].

Dengue in Sao Paulo state has field work centralized though
coordination by SUCEN, Superintendencia de Controle de Endemias
[Superintendency for Endemic Control]; in accordance with a regular
survey of the level of infestation by the mosquito _Aedes aegypti_,
the municipalities are classified into 4 groups: (1) with a dengue
epidemic; (2) infested [by _Ae. aegypti_] with dengue [virus]
transmission; (3) infested without transmission and; (4) not infested.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT <promed@promedmail.org>

[Taboao da Serra is part of the greater metropolitan area of Sao Paulo
city. An interactive map showing its location can be accessed at
