[6] Brazil (Mato Grosso do Sul)
Date: Fri 29 Jan 2010
Source: Fatima News [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.fatimanews.com.br/canais/noticias/?id=95672>


Dourados has now registered a dengue epidemic. The Epidemiological
Surveillance Nucleus of the municipal Secretariat of Health received,
as of yesterday [28 Jan 2010], notification of 379 dengue cases, which
represents an increase of 1805 percent in relation to last year
[2009]. The number of notified cases [over those] that are expected
for the period increased by 1263 percent, which characterizes the
municipal situation as an epidemic according to the statement by the
Nucleus. The incidence of the disease is 199.7 [dengue] cases per 100
000 inhabitants.

The majority of the cases are pending, awaiting the completion of
specific [laboratory] tests. Dengue virus serotype 2 was isolated,
which has circulated in the municipality since last year [2009].
According to the monitoring report, there is a growing predominance of
women among reported cases and concentration of those aged 20-49 years
(53 percent of the reported cases). The occurrence of cases in the age
group of children 14 years of age (44 cases, 12 percent of reports) is
showing a shift in age of occurrence of the disease.

Of the reported cases, about 40 percent were concentrated in 8
neighborhoods, but there have been reports of the disease in the
entire municipality, reinforcing the city's situation as epidemic. It
has been verified that the highest case indices have been displaced
from the Jardim Maracana region (1st half of 2009) to Grande Florida
(2nd half of 2009 and 1st half of 2010) and to Jardim Água Boa.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT <promed@promedmail.org>

[Notice: those who follow ProMED-PORT will grow tired of seeing dengue
posts. Patience -- as I commented earlier -- this is the year (2010)
of dengue. - Mod.LJS]

[In December 2009 in Dourados, 118 cases were reported, of which 40
were confirmed, and 58 were awaiting results of laboratory tests (see
ProMED archive no. 20100111.0131). The above report indicates that
there were 379 cases so far this year (2010) as of 29 Jan 2010. So the
outbreak continues and intensifies.

A map showing the location of Dourados municipality in Mato Grosso do
Sul can be accessed at
<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:MatoGrossodoSul_Municip_Dourados.svg>. -
Mod.TY]

[Brazil reported to PAHO a DHF rate of one percent up to
Epidemiological Week 30 of 2009, and the presence of dengue serotypes
1, 2 & 3. - Mod.JW]

