[8] Indonesia (East Java, Lumajang)
Date: Tue 26 Jan 2010
Source: Antara News [edited]
<http://www.antara.co.id/en/news/1264485967/two-die-of-dengue-fever-in-lumajang>


Up to 26 Jan this year [2010], 2 residents of Lumajang died of dengue fever.

"The number of dengue fever sufferers in Lumajang up to the 4th week
of January 2010 has reached 76 people, and 2 of them, both children,
were dead," Dr. Buntaran Supriyadi, head of the Lumajang district
health service, said here on Tuesday [26 Jan 2010].

Since the rainy season in December [2009], the number of dengue fever
patients has continued to increase, he said.

--
